token_lists.title: VESSELS CARAVAN CREW: THE QUIRKS
token_lists.description:
This rag-tag crew trundles from port to port in their rickety ship, The Quirk, (named for captain and founder Irk and her unusual crew). If you ask each member what their crew's purpose is, you'll likely receive five different answers, but one thing that unites them all is a love for the almighty coin. 

Whether you find them scavenging in scrap yards for old tech to refurbish and sell, or putting on an impromptu performance in a local pub led by their lion-bard, Shannon, or even engaging in some occasional criminal antics, they make sure to earn enough to ensure full bellies at the end of each night, as well as a little extra for booze and other diversions. 

Their beleaguered accountant Emawawa often begs them to set some funds aside for much needed ship repairs, but even he is subject to overspend when a casino is to be found nearby.

Their different personalities may clash at times, but like any crew, they're family. And each one of them knows that one day they'll discover a payload that will change their lives. It's just a matter of time....

Captain: Irk
Pilot: Ane
Mech: Osine
Bard: Shannon
Accounting: Emawawa

token_lists.title: VesselFlow: Black Neutrons (CHANDREW crew)
token_lists.description:
The darkness of space is precious to these black market traders.

Precious artifacts remain hidden until dedicated explorers unearth them.

That's when they make their way to the Chandrew, a mobile base of operations for the Black Neutrons. Its flight bays harbor small crafts, made to fly under the cover of the darkness of space.

Eventually, every artifact will land in the hands of wealthy collectors and traders with suitable liquidity. For the right price.

ROSTER
=======
Blakely: Captain, OpSec
Ormuntoth: Appraiser, 1st Mate
Nodypi: Pilot, OpSec
Aelae: Negotiator, Field Operative, Ops Planner
Needle: Esper, Navigator, CyOps

token_lists.title: Mumu's Crew
token_lists.description:
A crew of fashionable teenagers who infiltrate elite society in the colony, and fight for the rights of the oppressed and the abused. 

Haritsam with the green armor helmet and Omni Nibbler familiar is the fighter, who stays anonymous. No one know what she looks like.

Engaos is well respected in the colony, and champions the downtrodden. No one dares cross him.

Kawachi had been assaulted in the alleys of the colony before, but those who assaulted did not live to see another day. She is a fierce fighter who got her cyborg body after the attack.

Schmitt is the witch of the crew. She lays low and stays hidden most of the time. She is able to telepathically communicate with the rest of the crew, and see through the eyes of her Pigmy Hooter familiar. 

Fynida seems like a regular elite teenager who loves fun things like bunnies and tacos. But she hides a dark secret, a dark past, that has made her set on rebelling against the Queen.
